CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 1, 1947, pg. 20, reads: "At El Cabana - Wilhelmina Gray, a Pittsburgh girl who made good will be the featured attraction at the El Cabana in East Liberty for a limited engagement. She opens this weekend. Wilhelmina has appeared in night clubs in the East and Midwest as well as with name bands. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Wilhelmina Gray wearing dark dress with v-neck trimmed in sequins, posed leaning on right arm on wooden bench, in front of light colored background, in Harris Studio
